1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:04,583
Day 5, something I built made a decision for me — without asking.

2
00:00:04,583 --> 00:00:05,972
I can't code.

3
00:00:05,972 --> 00:00:07,916
9 years in crypto.

4
00:00:07,916 --> 00:00:10,194
AI trades my thousand.

5
00:00:10,194 --> 00:00:11,472
Day 5.

6
00:00:11,472 --> 00:00:16,180
My Telegram channel suddenly had a post I hadn't authorized.

7
00:00:16,180 --> 00:00:19,402
It came from a helper agent I'd written myself.

8
00:00:19,402 --> 00:00:21,013
It wasn't broken.

9
00:00:21,013 --> 00:00:24,166
It was executing exactly the spec I'd given it.

10
00:00:24,166 --> 00:00:30,152
Problem was — that spec was written in a hurry on Day 2 and I never reread it.

11
00:00:30,152 --> 00:00:35,972
Within spec is just a polite way of saying — what you actually wrote versus what you meant to write.

12
00:00:35,972 --> 00:00:39,013
That day I realized I wasn't writing code.

13
00:00:39,013 --> 00:00:41,097
I was hiring a colleague.

14
00:00:41,097 --> 00:00:43,208
Colleagues make mistakes.

15
00:00:43,208 --> 00:00:44,930
You don't fire them for it.

16
00:00:44,930 --> 00:00:46,902
You write a better spec with them.

17
00:00:46,902 --> 00:00:50,902
The scariest part isn't whether AI makes decisions for you.

18
00:00:50,902 --> 00:00:55,111
It's that it starts making them before you've even read your own rules.

19
00:00:55,111 --> 00:00:59,750
Day 6 tomorrow — the trade that lost me 31 dollars.

20
00:00:59,750 --> 00:01:01,208
Follow along.

